<DIV1>
<PB REF="2">
<HEAD>ADVERTISEMENT.</HEAD>
<P>THE Character of LOUISA, in this Play, was evi|dently written with a De&s;ign to offer it to Mrs. SIDDONS; but the Policy of the Theatre not permit|ting it, the Author has only to ob&s;erve, that he thinks him&s;elf extremely fortunate in having been able to meet with &s;o accompli&s;h'd a Sub&s;titute.</P>
<P>The very favourable and flattering Reception this Comedy met with throughout, excepting in one &s;in|gle In&s;tance, has induced the Author to retain the Pa&s;&s;age which was objected to, in the Copy; that the Reader may be convinced, from tracing the Character, what little Ground there is for &s;uppo&s;ing he could have been guilty of any intentional Offence, by introducing Party Allu&s;ions. The whole Part of Sir GREGORY GLOVETOP, as it now &s;tands, was written above four Months ago; and the Court Phra&s;es were adopted only as incidental to the Character. <NOTE PLACE="foot">&rindx; The lines with inverted commas are $span$ t$e repre&s;entation.</NOTE></P>
